{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62d1dfff-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s4184"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4184"},"text":"§ 4184.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Effect on HOME Investment Partnerships Act","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this chapter or an amendment made by this chapter prohibits or prevents any participating jurisdiction (within the meaning of the HOME Investment Partnerships Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12721"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 12721","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)) from providing any amounts made available to the participating jurisdiction under that Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12721"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 12721","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) to an Indian tribe or a tribally designated housing entity for use in accordance with that Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12721"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 12721","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id62d1e000-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/330/tV/s509"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–330, title V, § 509","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/411/tV/s501/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–411, title V, § 501(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/4331"},"text":"122 Stat. 4331","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id62d1e001-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id62d1e002-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id62d1e003-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/330"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–330","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-26"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/4016"},"text":"110 Stat. 4016","children":[],"tail":", known as the Native American Housing Assistance and Self-Determination Act of 1996. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s4101"},"text":"section 4101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The HOME Investment Partnerships Act, referred to in text, is title II of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/625"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–625","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4094"},"text":"104 Stat. 4094","children":[],"tail":", which enacted subchapter II of chapter 130 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1437f"},"text":"section 1437f of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", and repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1706e"},"text":"section 1706e of Title 12","children":[],"tail":", Banks and Banking, sections 1437"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":" and 1452b of Title 42, and provisions set out as a note under section 1715"},{"tag":"i","at